<|startoftext|>Dish: giada guarancona
Directions: saute garlic in olive oil in an uncovered pan over medium high heat for about 2 1 / 2 minutes or until tender
add onion slices and cook over high heat until translucent
do not allow to boil
stir in basil and black pepper and let simmer 10 minutes
add tomatoes
cook over moderate heat until tomatoes can easily thicken with any juice , stirring occasionally
add guarancona
return to a simmer , stirring occasionally for 20-30 minutes or until very tender-crisp
meanwhile , puree cornstarch in a separate bowl , add cornstarch mixture to tomatoes , stir and mix all together
return to the simmer for about 5 minutes until thickened , stirring constantly and adding more salt if necessary
serve over hot pasta
